########  Ways to access string characters  #######

####### 1. Index operator --> s[index] --> to access a single character from the string. 

s[1] # y


####### 2. slice operator --> s[begin:end:step]

# s[:end] --> begin is optional, default value is 0 
# s[begin:] --> end is optional, deafault value is len(s)
# s[begin:end] --> represnts a range of characters from begin to end-1

# s[begin:end:step] --> 
# begin and end values can be +ve or -ve.
# step is optional, default value is 1
# step value can be +ve or -ve but never 0. 
# If step value is +ve, then slicing is done from left to right. [Forward direction]
# If step value is -ve, then slicing is done from right to left. [Backward direction]
# Forward direction --> default value begin=0, end=len(s)
#                   --> if end=0, then the string is empty.

# Backward direction --> default value begin=-1, end= -(len(s)+1)
#                    --> if end=-1, then the string is empty.



######## 3. + Operator --> concatenation operator

