###### find(), rfind(), index(), rindex() --> to find the index of the first occurrence of a substring in the string.


### find(), rfind() 

# in java, we have indexOf() method to find the index of the first occurrence of a substring in the string. It returns -1 if the substring is not found in the string. lastIndexOf() method is used to find the index of the last occurrence of a substring in the string. It also returns -1 if the substring is not found in the string.

# in python, we have find() method and is used to find the index of the first occurrence of a substring in the string. It returns -1 if the substring is not found in the string. 
# rfind() method is used to find the index of first occurance of a substring from right side but index is always measured from the right side of the string. It also returns -1 if the substring is not found in the string.

# find(substring, start, end) --> to find the index of the first occurrence of a substring in the remaining string. It returns -1 if the substring is not found in the remainingstring.


#### index(), rindex()

# index() method is used to find the index of the first occurrence of a substring in the string. It raises ValueError if the substring is not found in the string.

print()
email=input("Enter your email: ")

try :
    index=email.index("@")            # can raise ValueError if @ is not present 
    print("Index of @ is: ", index)
except ValueError:
    print("@ is not present in the email")


# rindex() method is used to find the index of the first occurrence of a substring from the right side of the string or last occurance of the string. It raises ValueError if the substring is not found in the string.  

