########## split() and join() ############

# split() method is used to split the string into a list of substrings based on the specified delimiter. It returns a list of substrings. If the delimiter is not specified, then it splits the string based on whitespace. same as Java.
#split(Operator) --> to split the string based on the specified operator. It returns a list of substrings. If the operator is not specified, then it splits the string based on whitespace.

# join() method is used to join the list of substrings into a single string based on the specified delimiter. It returns a string. same as Java.
#separator.join(list) --> to join the list of substrings into a single string based on the specified separator. It returns a string. If the separator is not specified, then it joins the list of substrings based on whitespace.

s1="This is a sample string"
s2= s1.split() # default delimiter is whitespace
#s2=s1.split("-") # delimiter is "-"
print(s2) # ['This', 'is', 'a', 'sample', 'string']

s3= "-".join(s2) # delimiter is "-"
print(s3) # This-is-a-sample-string



